### ============================================================================
### Flexible Handler Patterns Example
### Demonstrates adaptSmart's ability to handle various handler signatures
### ============================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Pattern E: func(ctx) error - Manual control
GET {{baseUrl}}/departments

### Pattern A: func(dep, id string) (data, error) - Multiple string path params
GET {{baseUrl}}/departments/engineering/users/1

### Pattern A: Different department
GET {{baseUrl}}/departments/sales/users/3

### Pattern A: Not found
GET {{baseUrl}}/departments/engineering/users/999

### Pattern B: func(ctx, dep, id string) error - Context + multiple strings
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/departments/engineering/users/2

### Pattern C: func(req *Struct) (data, error) - Struct with path + query tags
GET {{baseUrl}}/departments/sales/users/search?q=charlie&page=1

### Pattern D: func(ctx, dep string, req *Struct) (data, error) - Context + path string + body struct
POST {{baseUrl}}/departments/engineering/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "David",
  "email": "david@example.com"
}

### Pattern D: Create in sales department
POST {{baseUrl}}/departments/sales/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Eve",
  "email": "eve@example.com"
}

### Verify new user created
GET {{baseUrl}}/departments/engineering/users/3

